defs.docs:
The enum [`Either`] with variants `Left` and `Right` is a general purpose
 sum type with two cases.

defs.name: Left
defs.docs: A value of type `L`.

defs.name: Right
defs.docs: A value of type `R`.

defs.name: Either
defs.docs:
The enum `Either` with variants `Left` and `Right` is a general purpose
 sum type with two cases.

defs.name: is_left
defs.docs: Return true if the value is the `Left` variant.

defs.name: is_right
defs.docs: Return true if the value is the `Right` variant.

defs.name: left
defs.docs: Convert the left side of `Either<L, R>` to an `Option<L>`.

defs.name: right
defs.docs: Convert the right side of `Either<L, R>` to an `Option<R>`.

defs.name: as_ref
defs.docs: Convert `&Either<L, R>` to `Either<&L, &R>`.

defs.name: as_mut
defs.docs: Convert `&mut Either<L, R>` to `Either<&mut L, &mut R>`.

defs.name: flip
defs.docs: Convert `Either<L, R>` to `Either<R, L>`.

defs.name: map_left
defs.value: fn <F, M> (self, f: F) -> Either<M, R>
defs.docs:
Apply the function `f` on the value in the `Left` variant if it is present rewrapping the
 result in `Left`.

defs.name: map_right
defs.value: fn <F, S> (self, f: F) -> Either<L, S>
defs.docs:
Apply the function `f` on the value in the `Right` variant if it is present rewrapping the
 result in `Right`.

defs.name: either
defs.value: fn <F, G, T> (self, f: F, g: G) -> T
defs.docs:
Apply one of two functions depending on contents, unifying their result. If the value is
 `Left(L)` then the first function `f` is applied; if it is `Right(R)` then the second
 function `g` is applied.

defs.name: either_with
defs.value: fn <Ctx, F, G, T> (self, ctx: Ctx, f: F, g: G) -> T
defs.docs:
Like `either`, but provide some context to whichever of the
 functions ends up being called.

defs.name: left_and_then
defs.value: fn <F, S> (self, f: F) -> Either<S, R>
defs.docs: Apply the function `f` on the value in the `Left` variant if it is present.

defs.name: right_and_then
defs.value: fn <F, S> (self, f: F) -> Either<L, S>
defs.docs: Apply the function `f` on the value in the `Right` variant if it is present.

defs.name: into_iter
defs.docs: Convert the inner value to an iterator.

defs.name: left_or
defs.docs: Return left value or given value

defs.name: left_or_default
defs.docs: Return left or a default

defs.name: left_or_else
defs.docs: Returns left value or computes it from a closure

defs.name: right_or
defs.docs: Return right value or given value

defs.name: right_or_default
defs.docs: Return right or a default

defs.name: right_or_else
defs.docs: Returns left value or computes it from a closure

defs.name: factor_first
defs.docs: Factor out a homogeneous type from an either of pairs.

defs.name: factor_second
defs.docs: Factor out a homogeneous type from an either of pairs.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Extract the value of an either over two equivalent types.
